race.comment: LYRICS 'N' SONG (9) looks clearly he one to beat. She's a very well-bred filly by Written Tycoon out of champion mare Melody Belle who was heavily backed on debut at Moonee Valley and tried hard when just edged out into second. Better for that and she should have these covered, especially given some dangers have come out. ECO EXPRESS (1) is a gelding by Alabama Express on debut who for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. He's been jumping out well enough to be a factor and the stable are always worth keeping an eye on with their newcomers.  SKJALDMO (13) was much better second up at Ballarat when getting home for a narrow fourth in a slowly run race. Up to 1200m should suit now third up. SILENT ANSWER (11) is a well bred filly on debut for the Stokes yard who can run a good race.
